  "prompt": "What is the best way to get change for the new 2000 INR note?",
  "response": "Getting change for a 2000 INR note can be done relatively easily, as it involves breaking it down into smaller denominations that are more commonly used for everyday transactions. Here are some of the best ways to do so:\n\n1. **Retail Stores or Supermarkets**: When making a purchase, especially at larger retail stores or supermarkets, you can usually pay with a 2000 INR note and receive change back in smaller denominations.\n\n2. **Banks**: Visiting a bank is a straightforward way to exchange a 2000 INR note for smaller denominations. Banks are equipped to handle such requests, and you can specify the denominations you prefer, such as 500, 200, 100, 50, 20, or 10 INR notes.\n\n3. **ATMs**: Some ATMs allow you to withdraw specific denominations. You can deposit your 2000 INR note into your account and then withdraw smaller denominations if the ATM has this option.\n\n4. **Local Shops or Vendors**: Small shops or vendors might be able to break a 2000 INR note if they have enough change on hand, especially earlier in the day when they have just opened. \n\n5. **Public Transit Stations**: Ticket counters at metro stations or bus stations often deal with a lot of cash and can provide change for larger notes.\n\n6. **Pay for Services**: Use the note to pay for services where the final bill is close to 2000 INR, such as dining out with friends or family and then getting the change back.\n\nRemember to always be polite and patient when asking for change, as not all places may have sufficient smaller notes readily available.",
